                            <comment id="52339" author="luke" created="Tue, 23 Mar 2010 09:09:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Converted patch to attachment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="52340" author="luke" created="Tue, 23 Mar 2010 09:13:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve made changes to treat an invalid header (either bad Base64 or an invalid token) as an authentication failure, which will generally result in the authentication entry point being invoked. Using Base64.isBase64() just decodes the encoded string an additional time which will not be necessary in most cases, so I&apos;ve elected to trap the exception raised when the characters are invalid instead, throwing BadCredentialsException.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
